      "date": "2026-05-28",
      "description": "US Consumer Confidence Dips Amid Inflation Concerns",
      "details": "The Conference Board's Consumer Confidence Index, a key measure of economic sentiment, fell to 98.5 in May from 101.2 in April. This index tracks how consumers feel about current business and labor market conditions, as well as their expectations for the next six months. A sustained decline suggests growing consumer anxiety about inflation and economic stability, which can lead to reduced discretionary spending on non-essential items like premium gifts.",
