      "description": "Gasoline Prices Hit New Summer Highs",
      "details": "The national average price for a gallon of regular gasoline surged to $3.85, a significant increase from the previous month and a typical summer peak. Rising energy costs directly impact household budgets, leaving consumers with less disposable income for non-essential purchases. This can disproportionately affect gifting, as consumers prioritize essential spending and reduce budgets for items like specialty foods.",
